result.execSummary:
The defendant James N Edwards was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

THE COURT ORDERED THE Defendant to pay a fine of $250.00 including all applicable costs and surcharges to be paid out of bail on deposit, if any; and the balance due on or before 04-01-2017.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.

Received and filed with the court:

Defendant James N Edwards in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant waived rights and pled GUILTY. Court found the Defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered. Parties are prepared to proceed with Sentencing.

Defendant James N Edwards in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea/Sentencing Hearing scheduled for January 19, 2017 at 08:30 am.  COURT WILL RETAIN FILE.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
